      { q: "What is the function of the sodium-potassium pump (Na⁺/K⁺ ATPase)?",
        options: ["Transports glucose into the cell", "Pumps 3 Na⁺ out and 2 K⁺ in per ATP, maintaining resting membrane potential", "Produces ATP via chemiosmosis", "Removes waste products from the cell"],
        answer: 1,
        explanation: "The Na⁺/K⁺ pump uses ATP to move 3 Na⁺ out and 2 K⁺ in against their gradients, keeping the inside of the cell negative and maintaining the resting potential critical for nerve/muscle function." }
